00:21.280 --> 00:22.480
It's beautiful.

00:22.680 --> 00:24.680
Thanks. It's the
children's ward, so...

00:24.960 --> 00:27.080
...I wanted it to feel
happy and full of light.

00:27.560 --> 00:29.080
It's incredible. You nailed it.

00:32.680 --> 00:34.080
And now that
you're seeing Peter...

00:34.280 --> 00:35.880
...everything's coming
together for you.

00:36.080 --> 00:37.080
Maybe, maybe not.

00:37.480 --> 00:39.960
I'm still not 100% sure,
more importantly...

00:40.880 --> 00:42.960
I miss you so much.
I really wish we...

00:43.280 --> 00:44.680
...got to spend
more time together.

00:44.880 --> 00:46.080
Me too.

00:47.280 --> 00:48.280
Licorice?

00:48.560 --> 00:50.360
No, I have given up sugar.

00:51.160 --> 00:52.480
-Sugar now?
-Yes.

00:52.880 --> 00:54.960
So no caffeine, no gluten,
and now no sugar?

00:55.360 --> 00:58.160
Peter says that sugar is
"nature's sweetest poison."

00:58.760 --> 01:00.160
I know. I read the book.

01:00.560 --> 01:02.480
It's impossible to
live by all of his rules.

01:02.760 --> 01:04.160
Well, he feels
you need to shift...

01:04.560 --> 01:06.360
...your mind in order
to shift your body.

01:08.080 --> 01:10.360
I would give anything to
spend one day with you...

01:10.680 --> 01:12.480
...where we just threw
caution to the...

01:12.880 --> 01:15.160
...wind and lived in the moment
like when we were kids.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.160
-What's going on?
-I don't know.

01:28.760 --> 01:30.080
Poor guy.

01:40.430 --> 01:41.710
Jaclyn Palmer...

01:41.910 --> 01:44.830
Peter? What's happening?
Are you okay?

01:45.630 --> 01:49.830
Five months ago today
was a magical day. My book...

01:50.630 --> 01:51.830
...Happy Heart Health, hit...

01:52.310 --> 01:54.030
...the New York Times'
best-seller list...

01:54.430 --> 01:58.030
...and you came to design the new
addition to the children's wing.

01:59.830 --> 02:03.110
I met you, and it was
practically love at first sight.

02:04.310 --> 02:06.510
I believe you are
the sweetest, smartest...

02:07.910 --> 02:12.230
...prettiest woman
I'm ever going to meet.

02:13.630 --> 02:15.030
Thank you.

02:16.910 --> 02:19.310
The most romantic day
of the year is coming...

02:19.630 --> 02:21.110
...and I can't imagine
spending...

02:21.310 --> 02:23.030
...another day of my
life without you.

02:26.430 --> 02:28.030
Will you marry me?

02:30.430 --> 02:32.030
On Valentine's Day?

02:33.310 --> 02:34.430
Just... just a second.

02:35.710 --> 02:38.310
This Valentine's Day?
Like, a week from now?

02:38.710 --> 02:41.710
Yes, I... I mean... I believe
that when you decide...

02:42.030 --> 02:44.910
No. When you know
you're going to spend...

02:45.230 --> 02:46.830
...the rest of your life
with someone...

02:48.310 --> 02:50.230
...then what's
the point in waiting?

02:55.030 --> 02:56.430
Yes?

02:56.630 --> 02:58.110
You said "yes,"
but you weren't sure.

02:58.310 --> 03:00.230
I mean, you were ambushed,
you had to say yes.

03:00.430 --> 03:01.830
Well, I was surprised.

03:02.030 --> 03:05.510
Do you hear how your voice
goes up at the end? "Yes"?

03:05.710 --> 03:07.710
Like you're asking a question?

03:09.510 --> 03:11.110
Look. Peter's a great guy.

03:11.630 --> 03:13.630
Any woman would be
lucky to marry him.

03:14.030 --> 03:15.710
I agree! He's an amazing man.

03:15.910 --> 03:18.430
He's a handsome,
successful cardiologist...

03:18.630 --> 03:19.910
...with a best-selling book...

03:20.110 --> 03:21.910
...but you've only known
him five months.

03:22.110 --> 03:23.710
Well, sometimes, you just know.

03:24.030 --> 03:26.230
Did you know statistics
say married people are...

03:26.630 --> 03:28.830
...happier and healthier
than single people?

03:29.430 --> 03:31.710
So marriage actually
lowers cholesterol.

03:33.110 --> 03:34.430
Yeah, I read chapter six.

03:34.710 --> 03:36.310
"Marriage makes a heart
grow stronger."

03:36.510 --> 03:38.230
I love that chapter.

03:40.510 --> 03:42.310
This has nothing to do
with Peter wanting...

03:42.510 --> 03:44.630
...to be named the new
Chief of the hospital?

03:44.830 --> 03:48.430
No! Well, yes, it probably
looks good for him...

03:48.830 --> 03:51.110
...to be settled down and
married in order to be...

03:51.510 --> 03:52.910
...considered for
the position...

03:53.230 --> 03:55.630
We are up... to 920,000...

03:55.910 --> 03:57.630
...views in one week?

03:58.230 --> 03:59.510
Are you in love with him?

03:59.710 --> 04:01.110
Does he make your
heart skip a beat?

04:01.430 --> 04:02.630
Does your stomach do flips?

04:02.910 --> 04:04.710
Do your knees get weak
when you see him?

04:05.230 --> 04:06.630
Well, I certainly hope not!

04:06.830 --> 04:08.830
Those are the first symptoms
of cardiac arrest.

04:10.630 --> 04:12.510
Kate... look...

04:13.230 --> 04:16.310
...I have dated some
real losers and I am not...

04:16.829 --> 04:18.230
...getting any younger.
-So...

04:18.510 --> 04:19.910
...you're making
the safe choice.

04:20.630 --> 04:22.110
What's wrong with that?

04:22.910 --> 04:24.110
Nothing, I guess.

04:25.030 --> 04:26.830
But don't you want to
plan your wedding?

04:27.230 --> 04:29.510
Peter's mother has arranged
for a small family dinner...

04:29.710 --> 04:31.910
...at this hotel where his
family's been vacationing...

04:32.110 --> 04:33.110
...for years.

04:33.310 --> 04:36.630
-So just a small, tasteful affair?
-Exactly.

04:36.830 --> 04:38.310
Like that?

04:48.330 --> 04:51.330
I thought this day would never
come, but here you are!

04:54.210 --> 04:58.010
You are the luckiest
girl in the world!

04:58.610 --> 05:01.210
-And Peter's a very lucky man!
-Of course!

05:01.410 --> 05:04.410
Peter's lucky, too. The Chief
of the hospital and his wife,...

05:04.810 --> 05:08.810
...the architect!
Now that is a power couple.

05:09.210 --> 05:14.610
And you must be our maid
of honor? Jaclyn's sister...

05:15.130 --> 05:16.410
-Kate.
-Kate!

05:16.610 --> 05:17.610
And you are our...

05:17.930 --> 05:20.130
...photographer, right?
Now, I was thinking that...

05:20.410 --> 05:22.810
...you could sneak the
photographs to the L.A. Times...

05:23.130 --> 05:26.010
...and they could publish them in
their high-profile wedding issue!

05:26.730 --> 05:28.730
You know, this is
really all too much.

05:29.010 --> 05:31.130
I told her you might not
want all this hoopla, but...

05:31.330 --> 05:33.130
Of course she wants it!
What bride doesn't...

05:33.330 --> 05:35.530
...want a fairy-tale wedding?
-Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:35.730 --> 05:37.130
Where's Peter?

05:37.330 --> 05:40.130
He's running. Now, this afternoon
you're gonna meet...

05:40.330 --> 05:43.130
...the rest of the family and then
tomorrow we're gonna have...

05:43.410 --> 05:46.810
...the wedding of my dreams
for you.

05:47.010 --> 05:49.530
Okay.
-Connie now, you come with me.

05:49.810 --> 05:52.130
There is a beautiful room
for the photographs...

05:52.410 --> 05:54.010
...and I think it will be just...

05:54.330 --> 05:55.330
Phillip!

06:00.530 --> 06:01.530
Honey!

06:02.410 --> 06:03.610
I hope you brought a hat.

06:03.930 --> 06:05.810
The sun is particularly
harsh this time of day.

06:06.210 --> 06:08.130
Peter, what is all of this?

06:10.930 --> 06:12.210
I tried to stop her, but...

06:12.530 --> 06:13.930
We talked about this.

06:14.130 --> 06:16.330
If I can't have time to plan
a wedding, then I just...

06:16.530 --> 06:18.530
...want something simple.
This isn't simple!

06:19.610 --> 06:21.330
This is...
I don't know what this is.

06:21.530 --> 06:23.330
Honey. You're right, okay?

06:23.930 --> 06:26.330
I'll talk to Mother and
get her to take it all down.

06:26.610 --> 06:28.130
Okay?
-Thank you.

06:28.530 --> 06:30.130
-I love you.
-I love you.

06:32.210 --> 06:34.330
Just that when she found
out how much I adored you...

06:34.530 --> 06:36.410
...she got a little excited
and went overboard.

06:36.610 --> 06:39.730
-I know. I'm sure she means well.
-She does.

06:39.930 --> 06:41.530
Why don't you go get rested up?

06:41.810 --> 06:45.010
I had them put that sparkling
water you love in your room.

06:45.530 --> 06:48.530
I am going to run two more miles
and then I'm gonna sit down...

06:48.730 --> 06:51.330
...with mother and tell her
to cancel everything.

06:53.110 --> 06:56.830
She will be devastated,
but she'll get over it.

06:59.110 --> 07:03.310
No. No. Don't do that.

07:04.430 --> 07:08.310
-Are you sure?
-Yes?

07:09.030 --> 07:12.110
You are the most thoughtful
person I know.

07:15.310 --> 07:18.510
Honey?
Only 300 steps today?

07:19.110 --> 07:20.910
I didn't have time to
run before the flight.

07:21.830 --> 07:24.630
Run for your heart, and
your heart will run for you.

07:32.030 --> 07:33.110
I like it.

07:33.430 --> 07:34.710
It's good, right?
-Yeah!

07:34.910 --> 07:36.430
Is that too corny
for a book title?

07:36.830 --> 07:39.110
No.
I think it's catchy.

07:39.310 --> 07:40.510
What would I do without you?

07:42.230 --> 07:43.510
I gotta go, I gotta go.
-Okay.

07:44.110 --> 07:45.430
Bye.

07:52.310 --> 07:53.910
Quick! What are
the first words that...

07:54.110 --> 07:56.110
...come to your mind
when you see this tent?

07:57.110 --> 08:00.110
I don't think that
I could put it into words.

08:00.310 --> 08:01.830
She could,
but she really shouldn't.

08:02.710 --> 08:05.230
A Valentine's dream.

08:05.910 --> 08:07.030
More like a nightmare.

08:07.230 --> 08:08.310
Mrs. Lorenzo...
-No.

08:08.630 --> 08:10.910
You must call me "Mama"
or "Mother" or "Mom,"...

08:11.230 --> 08:13.110
...whatever seems most
comfortable. Now, this...

08:13.310 --> 08:15.310
...is where the wedding
cake will go, and this...

08:15.510 --> 08:17.910
...is where you'll have your
first dance with Peter!

08:18.710 --> 08:20.230
Actually, I don't dance.

08:20.910 --> 08:23.110
At all. I'm...
I'm quite uncomfortable...

08:23.430 --> 08:24.830
She really doesn't.

08:25.030 --> 08:28.110
Not at her prom or at
birthday parties, weddings...

08:28.630 --> 08:30.030
You could skip the first dance...

08:30.230 --> 08:31.430
Nonsense!

08:31.630 --> 08:32.830
No, no, no, no, no.

08:33.110 --> 08:34.429
There's nothing to it.

08:34.710 --> 08:38.429
You just put your arms around
Peter's neck, and sway.

08:39.630 --> 08:41.710
I can't wait to show
you the bridal cabin.

08:42.510 --> 08:43.909
There's a bridal cabin?

08:48.130 --> 08:50.610
This is the bridal cabin.

08:51.810 --> 08:53.730
The hotel reserves it
for the bride and groom.

08:54.010 --> 08:55.930
I was lucky to get it
on such short notice!

08:56.530 --> 08:58.010
And I decorated it myself.

08:59.810 --> 09:01.210
So festive.

09:04.410 --> 09:06.210
Surprise!

09:07.210 --> 09:08.730
I know you didn't
have time to shop...

09:08.930 --> 09:10.610
...so I got it out of
storage and had it...

09:10.810 --> 09:12.930
...cleaned for you.
Believe it or not, I was about...

09:13.130 --> 09:14.410
...your size when I got married.

09:16.730 --> 09:17.810
I couldn't.

09:18.410 --> 09:21.210
I... I just brought
a simple white suit.

09:21.610 --> 09:25.130
This is a wedding!
You need a wedding dress!

09:29.130 --> 09:30.210
-What?
-Let's go.

09:30.410 --> 09:33.130
Let's give the bride a chance
to digest some of the...

09:33.410 --> 09:34.930
...special special-ness.

09:35.210 --> 09:36.730
You just relax, and try
that dress on!

09:36.930 --> 09:38.210
Okay.

09:43.730 --> 09:47.330
I want you to take some time
to think about this carefully.

09:49.210 --> 09:50.730
Is this really
what you want to do?

10:03.810 --> 10:06.730
Hi. Is there a bridal
store in town?

10:42.830 --> 10:44.030
Come on!

10:48.510 --> 10:49.830
Come on...

10:53.710 --> 10:55.310
You won't get cell
service out here.

10:58.110 --> 10:59.910
Thank you. I'm...

11:00.310 --> 11:01.910
...I'm... I'm just
looking for the town.

11:03.510 --> 11:05.030
It's that way about a mile.

11:05.830 --> 11:06.830
Great.

11:09.030 --> 11:10.030
And you're lucky.

11:10.230 --> 11:11.230
This time of day, the...

11:11.430 --> 11:13.710
...the bears are sleeping, so...
-Did you just say bears?

11:15.110 --> 11:16.310
I'm kidding.

11:17.230 --> 11:18.310
Good.

11:20.110 --> 11:21.430
Are you, you hurt?

11:25.430 --> 11:26.830
Here, let me have a look.
-Yeah...

11:27.030 --> 11:28.310
No! Thank you, no.I just...

11:28.510 --> 11:30.030
It's fine.
Just fell off the bike.

11:30.830 --> 11:31.830
I know first aid.

11:33.230 --> 11:34.830
What are you,
some kind of Boy Scout?

11:35.030 --> 11:36.430
Actually, yeah, I used to be.

11:36.830 --> 11:38.510
Great. Okay.

11:38.910 --> 11:41.310
I'm gonna go to town.

11:42.230 --> 11:44.230
I'll walk you. I'll make
sure you get there safe.

11:45.710 --> 11:46.710
You don't...

11:46.910 --> 11:48.310
You don't have to do that.

11:48.510 --> 11:50.030
Actually, I do have to do that.

11:50.230 --> 11:52.510
It's in the Boy Scout Handbook,
and I took the oath so...

11:53.230 --> 11:54.710
What about my bike? It's broken.

11:55.430 --> 11:58.510
Yeah, don't worry.
Bears don't ride bikes.

12:04.630 --> 12:05.910
It's so hot.

12:06.110 --> 12:09.310
Yeah, you know, we should really
be wearing sunscreen.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.510
Even with the tree cover...

12:11.830 --> 12:14.230
...the sun damage
this time of day...

12:26.830 --> 12:28.030
Why did you do that?

12:29.310 --> 12:30.510
What?

12:31.630 --> 12:32.830
Wha... That!

12:33.630 --> 12:35.110
I just wanted to
jump in the water.

12:35.510 --> 12:38.710
Well, that was a dangerous and
irresponsible thing to do!

12:39.910 --> 12:42.710
And do you always do the safe
and responsible thing?

12:43.110 --> 12:44.230
If you must know...

12:44.510 --> 12:46.310
...I don't like heights
and I don't swim.

12:46.910 --> 12:48.910
You don't trust yourself that
you'll be able to make the leap.

12:49.110 --> 12:50.830
You don't trust that
you'll be able to...

12:51.030 --> 12:52.510
...handle whatever might happen.

12:53.630 --> 12:54.710
That's complete nonsense.

12:58.430 --> 13:00.110
Clearly, you're
struggling with a decision.

13:00.310 --> 13:01.630
You're obviously preoccupied.

13:02.110 --> 13:03.230
You don't know that!

13:03.910 --> 13:05.030
This reminds me of a saying...

13:05.230 --> 13:07.030
...I heard once from
a wise old Italian woman...

13:07.430 --> 13:08.710
...and basically it
means you know...

13:09.030 --> 13:10.510
...a decision is
right when it feels...

13:10.910 --> 13:12.230
...like getting into a warm bath.

13:12.710 --> 13:14.110
Well, forgive me
if I don't want to...

13:14.430 --> 13:16.030
...discuss my personal
life with a stranger.

13:17.230 --> 13:18.510
That is precisely the reason...

13:18.710 --> 13:20.230
...why you should discuss
it with me.

13:20.430 --> 13:22.830
I'm a chance encounter with
a perfect stranger, whom...

13:23.030 --> 13:24.510
...you'll most likely
never see again.

13:24.710 --> 13:27.430
I'm in the unique position to offer
you unbiased, objective advice.

13:27.630 --> 13:29.830
You shouldn't eat those.
They might be poisonous.

13:30.230 --> 13:31.710
I hate to break it to you...

13:31.910 --> 13:34.510
...but you can do everything right
make all the right choices...

13:34.830 --> 13:36.230
...and still bad
things can happen.

13:37.630 --> 13:40.310
Well, thank you for all
of this stellar advice...

13:40.910 --> 13:42.430
...but I don't need
your help anymore.

13:46.110 --> 13:47.430
Which way do I go?

13:49.310 --> 13:50.910
Are you making this
decision because...

13:51.110 --> 13:53.310
...you think it's right or
because you feel it's right?

13:53.510 --> 13:55.630
Is it your heart or your head
telling you what to do?

13:56.430 --> 13:58.510
I met you an hour ago, and what?

13:59.430 --> 14:00.830
You think you know me?

14:01.510 --> 14:04.630
I... I know that you're...

14:04.830 --> 14:06.230
...you're thoughtful...

14:06.830 --> 14:10.030
...and... and kind...
and a little neurotic.

14:11.430 --> 14:13.430
Well, it's absolutely
arrogant to presume...

14:13.710 --> 14:15.430
...to know anything about me.

14:15.630 --> 14:17.630
Or my life!
Or...or any decis...

14:25.110 --> 14:26.510
Why did you do that?

14:28.230 --> 14:31.030
Impulse. I wanted to
see what would happen.

14:32.430 --> 14:36.230
Well, impulse is the lowest
form of human behavior.

14:37.110 --> 14:43.230
It's... impulsive, and...
immature and irresponsible.

14:45.430 --> 14:47.430
And I am very glad
I will never see you again.

14:54.630 --> 14:56.310
And another thing...

15:11.030 --> 15:13.230
There you are! Honey
where have you been?

15:13.510 --> 15:15.430
Mother and I have been
worried sick about you.

15:15.630 --> 15:17.030
What happened to your leg?

15:17.230 --> 15:20.030
I went for a bike ride in
the woods I fell off, I got lost.

15:20.630 --> 15:22.230
You poor thing.
Let me take a look.

15:23.310 --> 15:26.230
Surface abrasion. Well,
at least you got some exercise.

15:26.510 --> 15:28.830
I wanted to go into town to
look for a wedding dress.

15:29.030 --> 15:31.110
Mother said she's letting you
wear her wedding dress.

15:31.630 --> 15:34.030
Well, it's not exactly
my taste.

15:34.630 --> 15:36.430
Well, we don't want to
hurt her feelings.

15:40.430 --> 15:42.110
What about my feelings?

15:44.910 --> 15:46.430
Peter, does this seem
right to you?

15:47.430 --> 15:48.510
What?

15:48.830 --> 15:51.030
This! Us getting married
so fast.

15:51.830 --> 15:53.310
Are we making
this decision with...

15:53.510 --> 15:55.110
...our heads or our hearts?

15:55.310 --> 15:56.830
I don't understand
the question.

15:57.110 --> 15:59.110
Well, there's just so much
we haven't talked about.

15:59.310 --> 16:00.630
Like, where are
we going to live?

16:01.830 --> 16:03.110
Do we want to travel?

16:03.310 --> 16:04.710
Where do we want to
raise our kids?

16:08.110 --> 16:10.710
Kids? Do you want kids?

16:11.910 --> 16:14.030
I think so. Don't you?

16:15.910 --> 16:19.230
Look, we can discuss it.
If, in a few years...

16:19.710 --> 16:23.310
...you still want...
one, then we'll talk about it.

16:24.910 --> 16:26.910
We love each other,
and there is nothing...

16:27.710 --> 16:30.830
...we can't work through.
I just want you to be happy.

16:32.030 --> 16:33.310
That's so sweet.

16:35.230 --> 16:36.830
I think marrying
you is going to be...

16:37.110 --> 16:38.710
...the smartest decision
I've ever made.

16:46.910 --> 16:49.310
So then this scruffy
mountain man...

16:49.510 --> 16:51.310
...comes out of the
woods and tells me...

16:51.510 --> 16:53.110
...I need to abandon all
my decisions...

16:53.310 --> 16:55.030
...because I'm too responsible!

16:56.110 --> 16:58.110
How can you be
"too responsible"?

16:59.110 --> 17:00.630
Sounds like he really gets you.

17:01.910 --> 17:04.829
He eats poisonous berries
and jumps off cliffs...

17:05.230 --> 17:07.910
...but he thinks he can tell me
how to live my life.

17:08.230 --> 17:09.630
Okay, calm down. He's gone.

17:09.910 --> 17:11.630
You're never gonna
have to see him again.

17:11.829 --> 17:13.430
Well, I hope not,
because I would run...

17:13.630 --> 17:15.030
...the other way
as fast as I could.

17:15.230 --> 17:17.510
I would never give him a
chance to kiss me ever again.

17:17.710 --> 17:20.910
I'm sorry. You kissed him?

17:22.109 --> 17:26.109
No! No. He kissed me.
I didn't kiss him back.

