to go to bed.

39:14.310 --> 39:15.430
To sleep.

39:18.230 --> 39:22.910
Okay what I'm trying to say is
we need to go to our room so...

39:23.230 --> 39:25.110
...this day can finally end.

39:28.430 --> 39:30.830
So that we can look back
on our wedding day...

39:31.110 --> 39:33.030
...and be so happy that
we got married.

39:34.710 --> 39:36.110
-What?
-Please.

39:40.310 --> 39:41.310
This dress!

39:41.710 --> 39:43.710
We really should stay and
spend time with our guests.

39:43.910 --> 39:45.630
The bride and groom.
The bride and groom.

39:45.830 --> 39:47.310
The bride and groom.

39:59.630 --> 40:02.030
I think I'll go stretch out
under the stars for a while.

40:02.230 --> 40:03.310
Again?

40:04.830 --> 40:06.110
I could skip it.

40:06.310 --> 40:07.630
No, no, no, no, it's fine.

40:07.910 --> 40:09.510
Last night, you went
out on the porch...

40:09.710 --> 40:11.030
...and then
I went to bed alone.

40:31.510 --> 40:33.630
Please let this
day end forever.

40:47.430 --> 40:48.830
Hello?
-Good morning.

40:49.110 --> 40:50.310
This is your wake-up call.

41:06.310 --> 41:07.430
Good morning!

41:07.710 --> 41:11.310
Welcome to our wedding
day! Time to get at it!

41:11.710 --> 41:13.710
This is Kenneth and that's
Gerry, and they are...

41:15.110 --> 41:19.510
...going to transform you
into Cinderella.

41:27.030 --> 41:28.830
Well, she fell off her
bike yesterday and...

41:29.030 --> 41:31.310
...might have hit her head.
I think she has a concussion.

41:31.630 --> 41:34.830
-Maybe she's on drugs.
-I'm right here.

41:35.110 --> 41:37.110
I don't have a concussion
and I'm not on drugs.

41:37.630 --> 41:39.230
She recently gave up
sugar, caffeine...

41:39.430 --> 41:41.510
...and gluten, so she
could be hallucinating?

41:41.910 --> 41:43.910
Perhaps you should
all give us some space.

41:48.630 --> 41:52.430
I love you, honey. Remember,
for better or for worse.

41:53.630 --> 41:54.710
Okay?

41:56.030 --> 41:57.430
For better or worse.

42:02.230 --> 42:05.030
So... what's really
going on here?

42:05.510 --> 42:07.310
Well, there's nothing
wrong with me.

42:07.710 --> 42:09.230
I can see that.
You're perfectly fine.

42:09.430 --> 42:12.030
So why am I here? Cold feet?

42:13.430 --> 42:16.110
No! I'm not trying to
get out of the wedding.

42:16.430 --> 42:19.830
I am living the same day over
and over and over again.

42:20.030 --> 42:21.910
Every morning, I wake up,
it's February 14th...

42:22.230 --> 42:23.310
...and I'm getting married.

42:23.630 --> 42:24.830
I've seen this before.

42:25.310 --> 42:28.430
Are you serious?
Thank heaven.

42:29.110 --> 42:30.310
What do I do I fix it?

42:30.630 --> 42:32.710
Well, you're under a lot of stress
that causes anxiety.

42:32.910 --> 42:34.630
I'm gonna put you on
a mild antidepressant.

42:34.830 --> 42:36.510
No! No, no, no.
I don't have anxiety.

42:36.710 --> 42:38.430
I... Okay, well, yes, I do...

42:38.630 --> 42:40.230
...but it's not because
of the wedding...

42:40.430 --> 42:42.110
...it's because I am
living the same day...

42:42.310 --> 42:43.630
...again and again and again.

42:48.830 --> 42:51.910
-All right. Who's calling me?
-I don't know.

42:53.630 --> 42:55.030
Now you have a
credibility problem.

42:55.710 --> 42:57.230
If you were living the same day
again and again and again.

42:57.430 --> 42:58.630
You would know who's calling me.

42:58.830 --> 43:00.510
No, I wouldn't, because
that's not how it works.

43:00.710 --> 43:02.710
Every day's different.
I've never met you before.

43:03.910 --> 43:08.230
So you're living the same day
but it's different?

43:09.310 --> 43:13.310
-That's what I'm saying.
-That's what you're saying?

43:14.230 --> 43:15.710
I asked for a do-over.

43:16.710 --> 43:18.510
I just didn't think it
would actually happen.

43:19.030 --> 43:22.030
-A "do-over"?
-Yeah.

43:24.830 --> 43:25.910
I'm going to be right back.

43:32.430 --> 43:33.430
How's it going?

43:33.630 --> 43:35.430
She has to be in hair
and makeup by 12:00.

43:35.830 --> 43:37.430
I'm going to get
her tested for drugs.

43:38.030 --> 43:39.110
I'm still here.

43:46.430 --> 43:47.710
You okay?

43:49.230 --> 43:50.430
What are you doing here?

43:50.710 --> 43:53.030
Well, rumor has that you
went a little off the rails.

43:54.430 --> 43:55.510
Can you get me out of here?

43:57.230 --> 43:59.630
-Yeah.
-Okay, good, let's go! Come on.

44:05.630 --> 44:08.010
So if I get what you're saying
you're stuck in some kind of...

44:08.110 --> 44:09.630
...cosmic loop and you keep
living the same day...

44:09.930 --> 44:11.910
...over and over again?
How long?

44:12.810 --> 44:14.330
This is day four...

44:14.710 --> 44:18.230
I think. I don't even
care if you believe me.

44:20.310 --> 44:21.510
Well, I do believe you.

44:22.430 --> 44:23.710
You really do?

44:24.630 --> 44:26.110
I have no evidence
to the contrary.

44:29.610 --> 44:31.330
In the villages
I work in, in Africa...

44:31.530 --> 44:33.210
...they believe that
there is a whole...

44:33.410 --> 44:35.410
...world going on around
us that we don't see.

44:37.010 --> 44:38.330
And we're given clues that...

44:38.530 --> 44:40.210
...guide us in our
everyday lives.

44:41.210 --> 44:42.610
Some clues are harder
to understand.

44:44.130 --> 44:45.130
Maybe you're right.

44:45.330 --> 44:46.930
Maybe I'm in some
kind of cosmic loop...

44:47.630 --> 44:49.430
...and I just need
to break the cycle.

44:53.630 --> 44:54.710
Stay with me here tonight.

44:57.510 --> 44:59.510
Maybe if I never go
back to my room...

44:59.710 --> 45:02.030
...then the whole day
can't start all over again.

45:03.510 --> 45:05.430
Yeah, but if I stay
with you here all day...

45:05.630 --> 45:07.130
...you're going to
miss your wedding...

45:07.130 --> 45:08.810
...and my brother's
going to be heartbroken.

45:09.010 --> 45:10.610
Look, I already married
him several times.

45:10.810 --> 45:11.930
I'm not gonna do it again.

45:12.130 --> 45:13.730
So stay with me or
don't stay with me...

45:13.930 --> 45:15.010
...but I'm not going back.

45:15.530 --> 45:16.810
Peter loves you, and this is...

45:17.130 --> 45:18.130
Okay. Okay. Fine.

45:18.410 --> 45:20.410
If this doesn't work and
I can't break the cycle...

45:20.610 --> 45:22.130
...I'll marry him
again tomorrow.

45:23.330 --> 45:24.530
Okay.

45:27.730 --> 45:29.130
So we're stuck here all day?

45:32.530 --> 45:34.010
Might as well make
the most of it.

45:34.810 --> 45:36.930
I'm gonna help you get over
your fear of swimming.

45:38.330 --> 45:41.130
I don't have a fear of swimming
I have a fear of drowning.

45:42.530 --> 45:44.410
Have you ever heard
of immersion therapy?

45:44.730 --> 45:46.210
It's where you take
the person and expose...

45:46.610 --> 45:48.210
...them to what they're
afraid of, a little at a time...

45:48.410 --> 45:50.130
...till they get more
comfortable with it.

45:50.530 --> 45:53.410
-It's not gonna work.
-What have you got to lose?

45:59.210 --> 46:02.530
-I don't think I like this.
-It's okay.

46:02.810 --> 46:04.130
We don't have to go any further.

46:04.330 --> 46:06.130
Today, we can just hang
out in ankle-water.

46:08.010 --> 46:10.210
Your entire family must
think I'm a total nut.

46:12.330 --> 46:13.410
Then you'll fit right in.

46:21.330 --> 46:22.730
I'm so hungry.

46:24.610 --> 46:26.730
Do you want some of the
possibly poisonous berries?

46:28.330 --> 46:29.410
No.

46:29.810 --> 46:32.130
Well they didn't kill me yesterday
so they must be fine.

46:33.210 --> 46:35.810
True! Thank you.

46:40.610 --> 46:42.210
You know that eventually
you're gonna...

46:42.410 --> 46:44.530
...have to trust that
everything's gonna be okay?

46:47.530 --> 46:48.930
I'm so tired.

46:51.010 --> 46:52.410
But we have to
stay awake until...

46:52.810 --> 46:55.210
...it's tomorrow so the day
can't start all over again.

46:57.230 --> 47:01.310
Okay. How about this?
Go to sleep.

47:01.910 --> 47:03.030
I'll take the first shift.

47:03.430 --> 47:05.110
You take the next
shift. I'll go to sleep.

47:05.830 --> 47:08.030
That's a great idea. Thank you.

47:09.310 --> 47:12.710
And if it doesn't work, come
and find me, we'll try again.

47:45.310 --> 47:46.510
Hello?
-Good morning.

47:46.830 --> 47:47.910
This is your wake-up call.

47:48.230 --> 47:50.710
Why is this happening?
What did I do to cause it?

47:51.110 --> 47:52.710
Is there anything
I can do to stop it...

47:52.910 --> 47:55.110
...or am I completely powerless
over what's happening?

47:55.630 --> 47:58.830
Hello? Please, help me!

48:01.230 --> 48:04.310
Good morning! Welcome
to our wedding day!

48:05.110 --> 48:08.030
Time to get started. That's
Kenneth and this is Gerry.

48:08.230 --> 48:09.630
-Great. Great.
-And they are to...

48:09.830 --> 48:11.910
You can't transform me!
Nothing can!

48:12.110 --> 48:14.430
This is going to be
who I am forever.

48:14.710 --> 48:15.910
This one day!

48:16.230 --> 48:18.630
This is my past, my present,
and my future...

48:19.030 --> 48:22.510
...and this is not the
happiest day of my life!

48:30.110 --> 48:31.510
Can you get me 50
more of these?

48:43.910 --> 48:47.110
-Honey?
-Peter.

48:47.830 --> 48:50.510
Are you okay? Everyone's
really worried about you.

48:51.710 --> 48:53.830
It's bad luck to see the
bride before the wedding.

48:55.110 --> 48:57.430
That's exactly what I
wanted to talk to you about...

48:58.630 --> 48:59.830
....the wedding.

49:01.110 --> 49:02.310
Do you know we're supposed...

49:02.510 --> 49:04.110
...to be getting
married in an hour?

49:04.910 --> 49:07.230
I can't go through
with that wedding again.

49:08.230 --> 49:09.430
"Again"?

49:10.410 --> 49:12.610
It feels like we've been
getting married for weeks.

49:16.010 --> 49:17.210
Honey...

49:17.530 --> 49:19.530
Why are you so nervous?
We're a perfect match.

49:20.010 --> 49:22.010
We both love opera, golf
and crossword puzzles.

49:22.610 --> 49:23.930
Is that enough?

49:24.610 --> 49:28.210
I think I know what's happening
here and it's all my fault.

49:29.210 --> 49:30.210
It is?

49:30.530 --> 49:32.530
You have every right to
be confused and upset.

49:32.930 --> 49:34.130
I do?

49:35.410 --> 49:37.210
Thank you so much
for understanding.

49:40.410 --> 49:42.130
I just got so caught
up in my own world...

49:42.330 --> 49:43.930
...I forgot
I'm part of a team now.

49:44.610 --> 49:45.610
And I let you down.

49:46.010 --> 49:47.330
You did?

49:51.130 --> 49:53.530
My book was a
huge success and...

49:53.810 --> 49:55.330
...I became a
celebrity overnight.

49:56.610 --> 49:58.530
Now I'm about to be
named chief of the hospital.

49:59.330 --> 50:00.930
Soon, I'll be given
my own talk show.

50:03.730 --> 50:05.130
That has absolutely
nothing to do...

50:05.330 --> 50:07.010
...with what we're
talking about.

50:08.810 --> 50:10.730
Okay, look, if this is
about having a child...

50:10.930 --> 50:12.730
...I've thought about it and
I've come up with a solution.

50:12.930 --> 50:14.610
If, in a few years,
you still want one...

50:14.810 --> 50:16.410
...we can have a
child, and I'll film...

50:16.610 --> 50:17.610
...the whole thing
for my new TV show.

50:17.810 --> 50:19.010
The segment will be called...

50:19.210 --> 50:21.210
..."Be Heart-Healthy From
Conception to Delivery."

50:21.410 --> 50:23.930
You give birth,
and I deliver live on-air.

50:24.530 --> 50:25.810
No one's done that.

50:29.010 --> 50:30.330
Well? What do you say?

50:30.610 --> 50:32.210
We forget this whole
thing ever happened?

50:32.410 --> 50:35.010
You put on that wedding dress,
and we go get married.

50:43.130 --> 50:44.710
Hello?
-Good morning.

50:44.730 --> 50:45.730
This is your wake-up...

50:53.330 --> 50:56.210
Good morning! Welcome
to our wedding day...

50:57.410 --> 50:58.530
Where are you going?

51:06.010 --> 51:07.010
What are you doing here?

51:07.210 --> 51:08.530
Shouldn't you be getting
ready for your wedding?

51:08.730 --> 51:10.130
You promised to
help me get over...

51:10.330 --> 51:12.410
...my fear of water.
So... help?

51:17.330 --> 51:19.130
So if I understand you...

51:19.710 --> 51:21.830
...this day keeps happening
over and over again...

51:22.130 --> 51:23.810
...and I'm giving you
swimming lessons...

51:23.810 --> 51:25.210
...to help you get over
your fear?

51:25.410 --> 51:26.730
-Yes!
-But...

51:26.930 --> 51:28.530
...I don't remember
any of it because...

51:28.830 --> 51:30.710
...for me, this is the first
time it's happened?

51:31.010 --> 51:34.130
Exactly! So today,
we go in up to our knees.

51:34.730 --> 51:35.930
I'm doing very well.

51:37.210 --> 51:38.530
Well, then I think you should...

51:38.730 --> 51:40.610
...put your head in, maybe
float on your back.

51:40.810 --> 51:43.010
I don't think so.
But maybe tomorrow...

51:43.530 --> 51:46.130
Well, I guess today.
Maybe never.

51:48.330 --> 51:50.330
What happened that made
you so afraid of the water?

51:51.210 --> 51:53.410
You know, I wasn't always
scared of the water.

51:53.810 --> 51:55.410
As a kid, I went
swimming all the time.

51:56.330 --> 51:57.930
But then one day,
I just looked at...

51:58.130 --> 52:00.530
...the water and
decided it was unsafe.

52:00.930 --> 52:03.330
You know? It was
dangerous and risky and...

52:05.910 --> 52:07.510
...I know that doesn't
make any sense.

52:15.030 --> 52:18.110
Okay. Thank you for the lesson.

52:18.910 --> 52:20.230
I have to go get married now.

52:21.510 --> 52:23.430
Okay. See you at the wedding.

52:24.710 --> 52:26.230
By the way,
I love the speech that...

52:26.430 --> 52:28.230
...you're gonna make.
It's very sweet.

52:29.630 --> 52:30.910
I haven't written that yet.

52:34.830 --> 52:36.830
And tomorrow,
we go up to your waist!

52:37.910 --> 52:39.230
Fine.
I'll wear my bathing suit.

52:48.430 --> 52:51.230
I can't believe I went swimming!
I'm a swimmer!

52:52.230 --> 52:53.310
You're a fast learner.

52:58.410 --> 53:00.610
Actually, I'm not.
It's been days of lessons.

53:05.530 --> 53:09.330
-I was just scared.
-Yeah. We all are.

53:10.810 --> 53:13.130
It's what you do in spite of
your fear that defines you.

53:17.410 --> 53:18.730
Peter told me your parents...

53:19.610 --> 53:22.010
...they died in a car accident
when you were pretty young.

53:23.210 --> 53:25.210
They were just on their way
to the hardware store.

53:26.410 --> 53:28.010
I mean, if you can
die while going to...

53:28.210 --> 53:30.410
...pick up lightbulbs,
then nothing's safe.

53:32.130 --> 53:33.810
So that's when you
made the decision to...

53:34.210 --> 53:36.010
...play it safe, not to
take any risk, and...

53:37.210 --> 53:38.610
...live life by the numbers.

53:40.130 --> 53:42.610
And there's nothing wrong
with that. That's smart.

53:44.330 --> 53:45.930
Yes, but it's also an illusion.

53:47.730 --> 53:49.930
I hate to break it to you
but you can make...

53:50.130 --> 53:52.530
...all the right choices and
live life within the lines...

53:53.410 --> 53:55.610
...but life's still gonna
happen to you...

53:55.930 --> 53:57.330
...and you have
no control over it.

53:57.810 --> 53:59.530
Okay, well, I have
the illusion of control.

54:00.730 --> 54:02.330
What's the worst
that could happen?

54:03.610 --> 54:05.330
I don't know.
That's the problem.

54:06.810 --> 54:08.610
Yeah, but it seems
like you already...

54:08.930 --> 54:11.130
...went through the worst,
and you made it through.

54:17.210 --> 54:18.930
So if you could go
anywhere in the world...

54:19.130 --> 54:20.330
...where would you like to go?

54:21.410 --> 54:24.210
-Why?
-Just making conversation.

54:25.330 --> 54:26.330
Egypt.

54:26.610 --> 54:28.330
Cairo. I want to see
the pyramid of Giza.

54:29.730 --> 54:31.130
That's the one in the
middle, right?

54:31.330 --> 54:33.010
The biggest one?
It's still intact.

54:33.730 --> 54:35.130
It's actually
the oldest of the...

54:35.330 --> 54:38.210
...Seven Wonders of the
World. It's breathtaking.

54:39.210 --> 54:42.730
-You've been there?
-Yeah. Cairo's an amazing city.

54:44.530 --> 54:46.810
The architecture there is
still standing after so long.

54:47.410 --> 54:49.410
That's actually why I
wanted to be an architect.

54:50.510 --> 54:53.030
I want to be a part of something
that's here after I'm gone.

54:56.710 --> 54:59.030
Your wedding's happening
in a couple hours, so...

54:59.430 --> 55:00.430
No.

55:01.230 --> 55:03.030
I cannot go through with
that wedding again.

55:03.230 --> 55:04.830
I know your mother
means well, but it is...

55:05.030 --> 55:06.310
Okay, the dress...

55:06.510 --> 55:08.830
...the dress is wrong, the
flowers are horrible, the...

55:09.030 --> 55:12.230
...the cake is sugar-free,
gluten-free lemon.

55:12.910 --> 55:14.830
Who has a lemon wedding cake?
That's just sad.

55:15.430 --> 55:16.710
My first dance is humiliating.

55:17.110 --> 55:18.710
I can't dance, everyone's
looking at me.

55:19.710 --> 55:21.110
So learn to dance.

55:22.030 --> 55:24.230
No, I'm serious. Anyone
can learn to dance.

55:25.230 --> 55:27.030
My mother put Peter
and I in six years of...

55:27.230 --> 55:28.630
...dance classes
when we were kids.

55:28.910 --> 55:31.630
If I can teach you how to swim
I can teach you how to dance.

55:36.110 --> 55:37.110
What are you doing here?

55:37.310 --> 55:39.230
Shouldn't you be getting
ready for your wedding?

55:39.630 --> 55:41.230
You promised to teach
me how to dance.

55:41.510 --> 55:42.510
I did?

55:48.330 --> 55:50.410
Okay, so I'm gonna put
my hand on your waist...

55:50.810 --> 55:52.930
...you put your hand up here
on my shoulder. Good.

55:53.530 --> 55:54.610
I'm gonna step forward.

55:54.810 --> 55:57.410
You step back with your
right foot. And to the side.

55:58.210 --> 56:01.730
And back. And to the side.
Good.

56:02.530 --> 56:03.610
Now, if only we had music.

56:05.610 --> 56:07.730
Okay, not so tense.
Relax your shoulders.

56:08.210 --> 56:10.130
I'm still horrible!
I'll never get this.

56:10.930 --> 56:12.210
Well, it takes time.

56:12.930 --> 56:15.610
Be willing to let go of fear
and judgment, and just...

56:16.010 --> 56:17.730
...move to the music.
-Okay.

56:20.130 --> 56:21.530
Okay, close your eyes.

56:22.330 --> 56:24.730
Now I want you to go back to
when you were a little girl...

56:24.930 --> 56:26.810
...just dancing in your
room with your sister.

56:28.010 --> 56:29.610
There's no fear,
there's no judgment...

56:31.010 --> 56:32.730
...just the joy of
moving to the music.

56:36.210 --> 56:37.930
You know what?
When I was really little...

56:38.130 --> 56:39.330
...I wanted to be a ballerina.

56:39.610 --> 56:40.610
Really?

56:41.330 --> 56:42.930
I have no idea why
I just told you that!

56:43.130 --> 56:44.330
I have never told anyone that.

56:45.610 --> 56:46.810
Dancing is very intimate.

56:48.630 --> 56:50.710
Okay, you tell me something
you've never told anyone.

56:52.110 --> 56:54.310
And you had a huge crush on
your third-grade teacher...

56:54.510 --> 56:55.710
...and you never told anyone.

56:56.310 --> 56:57.830
What? How do you know that?

56:58.510 --> 57:02.110
I know about
Rachel and Lily and Malina.

57:03.510 --> 57:05.710
Okay, so I haven't
been very lucky in love...

57:06.510 --> 57:08.110
...but neither have you,
up until now.

57:08.510 --> 57:10.910
I mean, before my brother,
you dated some epic losers.

57:12.510 --> 57:15.510
-Wait! How did you know that?
-Cause you just told me.

57:25.110 --> 57:27.910
-You're a wonderful dancer.
-I had a great teacher.

57:28.710 --> 57:32.030
-And this is your first lesson?
